01:10.521 --> 01:11.996
Now I'm back here.

01:12.213 --> 01:14.546
So I'm sitting down, is that okay?

01:14.571 --> 01:16.003
Yes, ma'am.

01:16.527 --> 01:18.493
I'm Violet Roussard.

01:19.435 --> 01:21.502
I think I know you.

01:22.029 --> 01:23.971
You're that handyman
from the seventeenth.

01:24.007 --> 01:26.256
- Yes, ma'am.
- You fixed the railing

01:26.376 --> 01:28.817
- in the choir loft at Saint Amboys.
- How'd it do for you?

01:28.937 --> 01:32.527
It did us fine, until
this unnatural disaster.

01:32.615 --> 01:34.148
[Organizer calls]: All right, folks!

01:34.183 --> 01:37.118
I'm gonna be passing out a
displaced-persons fact sheet,

01:37.153 --> 01:39.656
and that's for everybody
ready to get on the next bus!

01:39.681 --> 01:41.515
Where's it going?

01:41.540 --> 01:45.008
Um... maybe Houston, or
Colorado, somewhere west, man,

01:45.128 --> 01:47.166
I'm not exactly sure, but
we'll get you outta here.

01:47.286 --> 01:48.885
All right, if you're
still waiting to meet up

01:49.005 --> 01:50.493
with missing family members,

01:50.613 --> 01:52.099
you've gotta put your name
on that board over there.

01:52.135 --> 01:54.049
The bus is leaving in five minutes!

01:54.537 --> 01:56.270
You lose anybody?

01:57.740 --> 02:00.044
I didn't have anybody to lose.

02:00.887 --> 02:03.955
